# rinfa

<!-- badges: start -->

[![Lifecycle:
experimental](https://img.shields.io/badge/lifecycle-experimental-orange.svg)](https://lifecycle.r-lib.org/articles/stages.html#experimental)
[![CRAN
status](https://www.r-pkg.org/badges/version/rinfa.png)](https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=rinfa)
<!-- badges: end -->

The goal of rinfa is to provide Rust bindings for parsnip model
specifications.

## Installation

You can install the development version of rinfa from
[GitHub](https://github.com/) with:

``` r
# install.packages("devtools")
devtools::install_github("simonpcouch/rinfa")
```

## Example

This uses the build in diabetes dataset

